# Go HTTP Server with Terraform

This project sets up a Go HTTP server that dynamically creates DigitalOcean Droplets using Terraform based on JSON input received via HTTP requests.

## Prerequisites

1. [Go](https://golang.org/doc/install) installed
2. [Terraform](https://www.terraform.io/downloads.html) installed
3. A [DigitalOcean account](https://www.digitalocean.com/) and API token

## Project Structure

go-http-server/
├── main.go
├── go.mod
└── terraform/
    ├── main.tf
    ├── variables.tf

## Setup

1. **Clone the repository**

    ```sh
    git clone https://github.com/your-username/repository-name.git
    cd repository-name
    ```

2. **Set up Terraform configuration**

    Navigate to the `terraform` directory and ensure the `main.tf` and `variables.tf` files are in place.

3. **Run the Go HTTP server**

    ```sh
    go run main.go
    ```

## Usage

Send a POST request to the server with the necessary JSON payload to create a DigitalOcean Droplet. Example using `curl`:

```sh
curl -X POST http://localhost:8080/terraform \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
  "digitalocean_token": "your_digitaltokenid",
  "image": "ubuntu-20-04-x64",
  "name": "first-project",
  "region": "fra1",
  "size": "s-1vcpu-512mb-10gb",
  "ssh_keys": ["your_ssh fingerprint"],
  "ipv6": true,
  "monitoring": true,
  "vpc_uuid": "your_vpc_uuid"
}'


